  * setup.py / setup.cfg
      - Add test module to manifest
      - python 2.5 uninstall?
      - Benchmark O1, O2, O0
      - setup.py: destination vs. configure (Arch)
         - setup.py install --prefix=/usr --root=tmp/pkg
         - Add a destdir option to install
         - finalize_options: x = os.path.join(destdir, x)
         - paths.py: if destdir: ...
      - Use intltool-merge for gaupol.desktop file translations?
          - See alacarte source code
      - setup.py: clean command?
      - Do setup.py install options work? Do they need to work?
          --prefix           OK
          --exec-prefix
          --home
          --install-base
          --install-platbase
          --root
          --install-purelib
          --install-lib
          --install-scripts
          --install-data

  * base
      - Use datetime.timedelta in calc
      - Version check timeout
         - http://aspn.activestate.com/ASPN/Cookbook/Python/Recipe/483752
      - Use action grouping in replace_both_texts(...)
      - Add exception handling for preview command being a blank string

  * gtk
      - Limit spell-check replacement file size
      - default paths.py relative source dirs os.path.dirname(__file__)
      - http://live.gnome.org/GnomeGoals/AppIcon
      - No need to check if translator-credits is translated
      - Unlimited undo by default
      - UIM name: /ui/menubar/edit/edit
      - Spell-check dialog mnemonics
          - Join _Back
          - Join _Forward
      - Redirect/copy sys.stdout to output window?
          - stdout: file-like object with a write(string) method
          - stdout.write(string): insert to text_buffer and scroll
          - sys.__stdout__.write(...)
          - http://diveintopython.org/scripts_and_streams/stdin_stdout_stderr.html
      - Adjust Durations dialog: Target
      - Menu item locations:
          - Framerate
          - Select Video
          - Headers
      - Remove Unselect All menu item?

  * Other
      - Check out Subtitle Editor's built-in preview

